title: SFH to visit Macau
content_text:
p>
			The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, will depart for 
			Macau tomorrow morning (July 31) to visit primary health-care 
			facilities, a hospital's acute care and rehabilitation service, and 
			a Chinese medicine research centre. During the visit, Dr Ko will call on Macau's Secretary for Social 
			Affairs and Culture, Mr Cheong U, and the Director of the Health 
			Bureau, Dr Lei Chin-ion, to exchange views on public health issues

Bureau, Dr Lei Chin-ion, to exchange views on public health issues 
			and matters of mutual concern, strengthening ties between the two 
			places. Health-care establishments to be visited by Dr Ko will include an 
			outlying island acute care services centre and the integrated 
			community medical centre of the Conde de São Januário General 
			Hospital. The acute care services centre provides 24-hour emergency 
			medical services while the integrated community medical centre 
			receives patients from Conde de São Januário General Hospital's

receives patients from Conde de São Januário General Hospital's 
			medical wards, nerve internal medicine department and department of 
			orthopaedics who are in stable condition and are expected to return 
			to the community in two weeks. In the afternoon, Dr Ko will visit a traditional Chinese medicine 
			science and technology park in Hengqin. He will tour an exhibition 
			hall to learn more about the latest developments in business 
			promotion and major projects on traditional Chinese medicine. Dr Ko

promotion and major projects on traditional Chinese medicine. Dr Ko 
			will then visit an elderly health centre in Taipa Island to see for 
			himself Macau's elderly health-care facilities. He will return to Hong Kong tomorrow night.
